### Variables
@host = http://localhost:8080
@phoneA = +33611111111
@phoneB = +33622222222
@phoneC = +33633333333

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### STORY CREATE-GROUP — Create a GROUP conversation
### ─────────────────────────────────────────
###
### Setup: 3 registered users (A, B, C). A must be friends with B and C
### (status ACCEPTED) otherwise createGroup will fail.
### A is the group creator. B and C are added as members.
### The creator is added automatically.
### ─────────────────────────────────────────


### 1. Register user A
POST {{host}}/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "Alice",
  "password": "test123",
  "phoneNumber": "{{phoneA}}",
  "email": "alice@test.com"
}

### 2. Register user B
POST {{host}}/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "Bob",
  "password": "test123",
  "phoneNumber": "{{phoneB}}",
  "email": "bob@test.com"
}

### 3. Register user C
POST {{host}}/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "Charlie",
  "password": "test123",
  "phoneNumber": "{{phoneC}}",
  "email": "charlie@test.com"
}

### 4. Login Alice (creator)
POST {{host}}/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "{{phoneA}}",
  "password": "test123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("tokenA", response.body.trim().replace(/^"|"$/g, ""));
%}


### 4b. Login Bob
POST {{host}}/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "{{phoneB}}",
  "password": "test123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("tokenB", response.body.trim().replace(/^"|"$/g, ""));
%}


### 4c. Login Charlie
POST {{host}}/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "{{phoneC}}",
  "password": "test123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("tokenC", response.body.trim().replace(/^"|"$/g, ""));
%}


### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### Friendship setup: Alice <-> Bob, Alice <-> Charlie (NOT Bob <-> Charlie)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### 4d. Alice sends friend request to Bob
POST {{host}}/api/friendships
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenA}}

{
  "phoneNumber": "{{phoneB}}"
}

### 4e. Bob fetches received requests
GET {{host}}/api/friendships/received
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

> {%
    client.global.set("friendshipIdAB", response.body[0].id);
%}

### 4f. Bob accepts
POST {{host}}/api/friendships/{{friendshipIdAB}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}


### 4g. Alice sends friend request to Charlie
POST {{host}}/api/friendships
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenA}}

{
  "phoneNumber": "{{phoneC}}"
}

### 4h. Charlie fetches received requests
GET {{host}}/api/friendships/received
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenC}}

> {%
    client.global.set("friendshipIdAC", response.body[0].id);
%}

### 4i. Charlie accepts
POST {{host}}/api/friendships/{{friendshipIdAC}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenC}}


### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### Happy path
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### 5. Alice creates a group with Bob and Charlie (expects 201)
POST {{host}}/api/conversations
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenA}}

{
  "name": "Vacances 2026",
  "memberPhoneNumbers": ["{{phoneB}}", "{{phoneC}}"]
}

> {%
    client.global.set("groupId", response.body.conversationId);
%}


### 6. Alice lists her conversations — should see the group with name="Vacances 2026"
GET {{host}}/api/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenA}}


### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### Edge cases / errors
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### 7. Empty name (expects 400)
POST {{host}}/api/conversations
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenA}}

{
  "name": "",
  "memberPhoneNumbers": ["{{phoneB}}"]
}


### 8. Empty member list (expects 400)
POST {{host}}/api/conversations
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenA}}

{
  "name": "Solo",
  "memberPhoneNumbers": []
}


### 9. Only person listed = the creator (expects 400 - one-person group)
POST {{host}}/api/conversations
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenA}}

{
  "name": "Just me",
  "memberPhoneNumbers": ["{{phoneA}}"]
}


### 10. One of the members does not exist (expects 404)
POST {{host}}/api/conversations
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenA}}

{
  "name": "Ghost group",
  "memberPhoneNumbers": ["{{phoneB}}", "+33699999999"]
}


### 10b. One of the members is not friends with the creator
###      Bob tries to add Charlie, but they are NOT friends with each other
###      (Alice is the common friend but is not involved here)
###      → expects 404 (FriendshipNotFoundException)
POST {{host}}/api/conversations
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

{
  "name": "Without Alice",
  "memberPhoneNumbers": ["{{phoneC}}"]
}


### 11. No token (expects 401)
POST {{host}}/api/conversations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "No auth",
  "memberPhoneNumbers": ["{{phoneB}}"]
}


### 12. Creator listed in members: ignored, group is still created
###     (expects 201 — the creator entry is deduplicated)
POST {{host}}/api/conversations
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenA}}

{
  "name": "With myself",
  "memberPhoneNumbers": ["{{phoneA}}", "{{phoneB}}"]
}


### 13. Duplicates in the list: automatically deduplicated
###     (expects 201 — the group contains 1 creator + 1 other member = 2 total)
POST {{host}}/api/conversations
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenA}}

{
  "name": "With duplicates",
  "memberPhoneNumbers": ["{{phoneB}}", "{{phoneB}}", "{{phoneB}}"]
}